[{"id":"VR024547","type":"mcq","stimulusHtml":"<div>\n<div class=\"stimulus_reference\">\n<div class=\"standalone_image\"><img alt=\"The figure presents a diagram of a circuit with a vertical branch in the middle and top end point of the branch is labeled as B. The left side of the circuit has a battery labeled 30 volts. The wire that extends from the battery ends after bending to the right at point A. The top of the circuit has a switch shown at position B, and would be closed at position A, and a resistor labeled 5.0 kilo-ohms. The right side of the circuit has a capacitor labeled 40 microfarads.   \" height=\"99\" src=\"https://assets.learnosity.com/organisations/537/VR024547.g03.png\" width=\"280\" /></div>\n</div>\n</div>\n\n<p class=\"stem_paragraph\">The capacitor in the circuit represented above is uncharged when the switch is at position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"B\"><math alttext=\"B\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>B</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. The switch is then moved to position <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"A\"><math alttext=\"A\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mtext>A</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span>. What is the energy stored by the capacitor when the current in the circuit is <span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"2.0 milliamps\"><math alttext=\"2.0 milliamps\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>2.0</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.3em\"></mspace><mo>⁢</mo><mtext>mA</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span> ?</p>\n","rubricRef":"VR024547_rubric","choicesHtml":["<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"0.8 millijoule\"><math alttext=\"0.8 millijoule\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>0.8</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.3em\"></mspace><mo>⁢</mo><mtext>mJ</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"1.2 millijoules\"><math alttext=\"1.2 millijoules\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>1.2</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.3em\"></mspace><mo>⁢</mo><mtext>mJ</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"8.0 millijoules\"><math alttext=\"8.0 millijoules\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>8.0</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.3em\"></mspace><mo>⁢</mo><mtext>mJ</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"16 millijoules\"><math alttext=\"16 millijoules\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>16</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.3em\"></mspace><mo>⁢</mo><mtext>mJ</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>","<p class=\"choice_paragraph\"><span class=\"math_expression\"><span aria-label=\"18 millijoules\"><math alttext=\"18 millijoules\" overflow=\"scroll\"><mstyle><mrow><mn>18</mn><mspace depth=\"0.0ex\" height=\"0.0ex\" width=\"0.3em\"></mspace><mo>⁢</mo><mtext>mJ</mtext></mrow></mstyle></math></span></span></p>"],"answer":2}]